name: E-commerce-Microservices-Application
description: Developed a scalable microservices-based platform with 7 independent services (e.g., Product, Cart, Payment).

name: TrailServiceApplication
description: The TrailService micro-service manages trail-related information, including trail details, waypoints, authors, and audit logs. It provides CRUD operations and integrates with an Authenticator API for user validation. This service is a core component of the Trail Application, enabling seamless data management and secure access.

name: Go-lang-Micro-service
description: Microservices Architecture with Go Explore the development of a microservices architecture using Go (Golang) to build scalable, reliable, and maintainable web applications. This project demonstrates the design and implementation of multiple self-contained microservices that communicate seamlessly through REST APIs, RPC over gRPC, and message queuin

name: Microservice-Social-Media-Application-using-RabbitMQ
description: A MERN-Stack powered Social Media Application | Remotely hosted on an AWS EC2 instance | Employs a CI/CD pipeline for automate deployments | Implements Microservice Architecture under Event Driven Architecture using Message Queues | PostgreSQL with Sequelize ORM for user-service| Implements Websockets using Socket.io for a real-time communication

name: Microservice-architecture
description: Application with service discovery, api gateway and users function. I also include creation of session tokens

name: ecommerce-microservice-backend
description: A e-commerce application that demonstrates implementation of a microservice using eureka and spring cloud for service communications

name: bot-jump-service
description: A micro-ROS project enabling a bot to jump using ROS 2 services. Commands are sent from ROS 2 to micro-ROS, which controls hardware with pneumatics via a relay to trigger the jump. Ideal for real-time actuator control in robotics applications.

name: MicroMall
description: MicroShop is a scalable e-commerce backend built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB, following a microservices architecture. This project demonstrates the separation of concerns by dividing the application into distinct services for handling products, users, and orders.

name: ingram-micro-sdk-js
description: NON-OFFICIAL - This project is an Express.js application that integrates with the Ingram Micro SDK for resellers. It provides various API endpoints to interact with Ingram Micro's services.
